  "items": [
    {
      "name": "Elemental Wisp (Rage of Elements) (Fire)",
      "type": "action",
      "effects": [],
      "system": {
        "description": {
          "gm": "",
          "value": "<p><strong>Required Number of Abilities 3</strong><br /><strong>Granted Abilities</strong> @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.familiar-abilities.92lgSEPFIDLvKOCF]{Accompanist}, @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.familiar-abilities.ch6nFcRJO1fm8B4D]{Elemental}, @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.familiar-abilities.zyMRLQnFCQVpltiR]{Speech}</p>\n<hr />\n<p>Wisps are tiny elementals that often act as familiars. They each usually have different personalities: air wisps are playful and capricious, earth wisps are timid but loyal, fire wisps are carefree and boisterous, metal wisps are serious and morose, water wisps are gentle and nurturing, and wood wisps are fierce and controlling.</p>\n<p><strong>Elemental Mobility</strong></p>\n<p>Your wisp gains a familiar ability depending on its element. Air wisps gain @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.familiar-abilities.ZHSzNt3NxkXbj1mI]{Flier}, earth wisps gain @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.familiar-abilities.uy15sDBuYNK48N3v]{Burrower}, fire wisps gain @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.familiar-abilities.fhyQ6uTSvfErTzyE]{Jet}, metal wisps gain @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.familiar-abilities.q9IXWngAOCpsXxsO]{Levitator}, water wisps gain @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.familiar-abilities.A0C86V3MUECpX5jd]{Amphibious}, and wood wisps gain @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.familiar-abilities.dWTfO5WbLkD5mw2H]{Climber}.</p>\n<p><strong>Innate Element</strong></p>\n<p>An elemental wisp's element is set. You choose the element when you gain the specific familiar and can't change it each day.</p>\n<p>@UUID[Compendium.pf2e-specific-familiars.specific-familiars-abilities.Item.co7ukp3X71Nk220E]{Resonance} (Aura)</p>\n<p>30 feet. <br />Your wisp vibrates at a frequency attuned to their element, resonating with and empowering all effects sharing that trait. Creatures in the area gain a +1 status bonus to damage rolls for alchemical and magical effects with the same elemental trait as your wisp. If your wisp is a wood wisp, the status bonus also applies to damage rolls for effects with the plant trait.</p>"
        },
